      <head>Richard von Kralik</head>

      <div>
        <p>Independent writer, music and theater critic, and author of historical works.</p>

        <p>Kralik lived in Vienna from 1870, and taught "aesthetics of church music" at the Vienna
          Akademie für Musik und darstellende Kunst (= Conservatory) from 1910 to 1923. He was an
          influential representative of catholic-conservative values, and enjoyed a high posthumous
          reputation in the Austro-fascist corporative state (1934-38).</p>
      </div>
